<p>Publish at least 2 to 4 blog posts per month. Consistency matters more than volume. Each post should target one primary keyword and include 3 to 5 <a href="/blog/internal-linking-blog-posts/">internal links</a> to related content on your site.</p>
<h3>The IDX Duplicate Content Problem</h3>
<p>IDX (Internet Data Exchange) pages display MLS listings on your website. The problem: hundreds of other agents display the exact same listings with the exact same descriptions. This creates massive duplicate content issues.</p>
<p>Fixes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add unique descriptions to featured listings (your personal commentary, not the MLS copy)</li>
<li>Use <code>noindex</code> tags on bulk IDX search result pages</li>
<li>Keep individual listing pages indexed only if you add unique content</li>
<li>Create unique neighborhood landing pages that link to IDX-filtered results</li>
<li>Use canonical tags to consolidate duplicate listing URLs</li>
</ul>
